# Backend Architecture Rules

## 1. Architectural Style

Backend MUST follow Clean Architecture.

---

## 2. Layers

### Domain Layer (CORE)

Responsibilities:
- Entities
- Value Objects
- Domain Errors
- Interfaces (contracts)

Rules:
- Must be framework-agnostic
- Must NOT contain I/O logic
- Must NOT depend on other layers

---

### Application Layer (STRICT)

Responsibilities:
- Use cases
- Business logic

MANDATORY:
- Business logic MUST live here

❌ FORBIDDEN:
- Delegating business logic to services
- Creating “service layer” for business rules
- Thin orchestration-only application layer

---

### Infrastructure Layer

Responsibilities:
- DB, APIs, external systems
- Implements interfaces from Domain/Application

Rules:
- Must NOT contain business logic
- Must NOT define domain rules

---

### Presentation Layer

Responsibilities:
- Controllers / API endpoints

Rules:
- Must be thin
- Must call application layer only
- Must NOT contain business logic

---

## 3. Dependency Rule

Dependencies must always point inward:

Presentation → Application → Domain  
Infrastructure → Domain/Application (via interfaces)

---

## 4. Domain Integrity Rule

Domain MUST remain pure:

❌ No frameworks  
❌ No DB logic  
❌ No HTTP logic  

---

## 5. Dependency Injection Rule

- All dependencies must be injected
- No direct instantiation inside Application/Domain